What is a Digital Farming System?
A Digital Farming System is a comprehensive technology platform that combines connected farm machinery, sensors, drones, satellite imagery, artificial intelligence, and farm management software to optimize agricultural operations. These systems collect, analyze, and convert field data into actionable insights, enabling farmers to make informed decisions on planting, irrigation, fertilization, pest management, harvesting, and regulatory compliance.
Modern digital farming platforms integrate field devices, cloud-based analytics, and precision agriculture applications into a single ecosystem. By improving operational efficiency and resource utilization, these solutions help farmers maximize crop yields while reducing water consumption, fertilizer use, labor dependency, and environmental impact.
